---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/layout/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/layout/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Knicknaks"
  description="Terms of service and usage rules for Knicknaks."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col w-full">
    <Header />

    <main class="flex-1 doodle-paper py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-8 font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--text-primary)]"
        >
          <span class="doodle-underline">Terms of Service</span>
        </h1>

        <div
          class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-[var(--text-secondary)]"
        >
          <p class="lead mb-8">
            By accessing and using Knicknaks, you agree to these fundamental
            rules. Keep it legal, keep it safe.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>
            Knicknaks provides free utility tools for developers, designers, and
            general users. You agree to use this website only for lawful
            purposes. You are strictly prohibited from using our services to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Facilitate illegal activities.</li>
            <li>
              Generate, format, or process data intended to cause harm, harass,
              or defraud others.
            </li>
            <li>
              Bypass security controls on other systems or engage in malicious
              hacking.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>2. No Warranty</h2>
          <p>
            The tools provided on Knicknaks run locally in your browser and are
            provided on an <strong>"AS IS"</strong> and <strong
              >"AS AVAILABLE"</strong
            > basis, without any warranties of any kind, either express or implied.
          </p>
          <p>
            While we strive for accuracy, we do not guarantee that our tools
            (such as generators, converters, or calculators) will always be 100%
            error-free. You are solely responsible for verifying the output
            before relying on it for production-critical systems, legal
            documents, or financial calculations.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Liability Limitation</h2>
          <p>
            In no event shall Knicknaks, its creators, or contributors be liable
            for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
            punitive damages arising out of your use of, or inability to use,
            our tools. Because all processing occurs locally on your machine,
            you assume all risks associated with the data you process.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Modifications to Service</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any tool or
            feature on Knicknaks at any time without notice. We are providing a
            free service and cannot guarantee permanent availability of any
            specific utility.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm mt-12 opacity-70">Last updated: March 6, 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
